# 3️⃣ AWARD DECISION CONTROL LOGIC

---

## 🔹 A. Rule Consistency Enforcement

System verifies:

* Winning bid has highest final score (or lowest evaluated cost)
* All mandatory requirements met
* No unresolved risk flags (Logic 9)
* Evaluation panel completed scoring properly
* No unauthorized scoring changes

If deviation occurs:

```
System blocks award → Escalation required
```

---

## 🔹 B. Tie-Breaker Logic

Pre-configured rules such as:

* Higher technical score prevails
* Local SME preference
* Lower lifecycle cost
* Earlier submission timestamp

Tie-breaker must be pre-defined in Logic 3 and cannot be changed post-bid opening.

---

## 🔹 C. Disqualification Confirmation

Before award:

System re-checks:

* Compliance documents validity
* Financial capacity thresholds
* Conflict-of-interest declarations
* Sanctions screening
* Blacklist status

---

# 4️⃣ APPROVAL WORKFLOW STRUCTURE

Award must pass internal governance levels based on:

| Contract Value | Required Approval   |
| -------------- | ------------------- |
| Low            | Procurement Officer |
| Medium         | Department Head     |
| High           | Executive Committee |
| Strategic      | Board / Ministerial |

System enforces:

* Sequential approval
* Digital signature logging
* No bypassing workflow

All decisions time-stamped.

---

# 5️⃣ AWARD NOTIFICATION LOGIC

Once approved:

---

## 🔹 A. Winning Supplier Notification

Includes:

* Final evaluated price
* Contract summary
* Acceptance deadline
* Required documentation
* Performance security requirement (if applicable)

---

## 🔹 B. Unsuccessful Bidder Notification

Includes:

* Notification of non-selection
* Summary of evaluation outcome
* Their score (if policy allows)
* Appeal process instructions
* Standstill period duration

Supports transparency and dispute mitigation.

---

# 6️⃣ STANDSTILL PERIOD (FOR PUBLIC PROCUREMENT)

Optional but critical in regulated systems.

Purpose:

* Allow unsuccessful bidders to challenge award
* Prevent immediate contract signing

Flow:

```
Award Announced
↓
Standstill Countdown (e.g., 10 days)
↓
If No Formal Challenge → Proceed
If Challenge Filed → Suspend Contract Formation
```

---

# 7️⃣ CONTRACT GENERATION LOGIC

---

## 🔹 A. Automated Contract Drafting

System pulls:

* Tender specifications (Logic 3)
* Winning bid details (Logic 6)
* Negotiated clarifications (if allowed)
* Standard contract template
* Applicable legal jurisdiction
* Pricing structure

Auto-generates structured contract document.

---

## 🔹 B. Contract Types Supported

* Fixed-price contract
* Framework agreement
* Unit-rate contract
* Milestone-based payment contract
* Service-level agreement (SLA)
* Call-off contract under framework

---

# 8️⃣ CONTRACT VALIDATION CHECKS

Before signing:

* Contract matches tender terms (no material deviation)
* Price matches awarded amount
* Scope unchanged
* Delivery schedule consistent
* Performance guarantees included
* Insurance requirements validated

System blocks modification of material conditions post-award unless formally justified.

---

# 9️⃣ DIGITAL SIGNATURE and LEGAL FORMATION

---

## 🔹 A. Signature Workflow

```
Buyer Authorized Signatory
↓
Supplier Authorized Signatory
↓
Contract Locked
```

Features:

* Multi-factor authentication
* Time-stamped signing
* IP logging
* Document hash fingerprint
* Version freeze after signing

---

## 🔹 B. Contract Activation

Triggered when:

* Both parties sign
* Required securities submitted
* Insurance verified
* Standstill period expired (if applicable)

System status changes to:

```
ACTIVE CONTRACT
```

---

